title: Middle school swimmers, divers place sixth at conference meet
text:
Middle school swimmers, divers place sixth at conference meet By Debbie Holmes 
Trail-Gazette Posted: 10/07/2015 10:02:34 AM MDT Steele Wolf, seen here swimming at last week's Bill Reed Invite, place dthird in the 200 freestyle event at the conference meet on Saturday. ( Debbie Holmes / Estes Park Trail-Gazette ) 
The Estes Park Middle School swimmers and divers competed in the end-of-season conference championship meet on Saturday, Oct. 3. 
The young Cat team of 17 held its own against many larger teams in the conference. There were many personal best times set by Estes athletes. 
Top 16 finishes for the Bobcats included: 
Steele Wolf had the highest finishes in the competition. He finished third in the 200 free (2:18.14) and fifth in the 500 free (6:24.84). 
John Ferree sprinted to a fourth place finish in his 100 breast (1:30.27) and 13th in the 50 free (33.75). Nathan Richardson tied his teammate, swimming from the opposite end of the pool with a 13th place finish in the 50 free (33.75) and was ninth in the 100 free (1:14.41). They were joined by Nathan Fitzpatrick for a fifth-place finish in the 200 medley relay. 
Fitzpatrick finished 11th in the 100 free (1:16.49) and fourth place in diving (143.64). Ben Ferree brought home a fifth place finish in diving (119.85) and 16th in 50 free (33:93). Amelia Westley finished seventh overall in diving (142.73). 
The team of Fitzpatrick, John Ferree, Ben Ferree and Wolf finished seventh in the 200 free relay (2:16.98). 
Zoe Hester grabbed seventh place in a personal best 100 breaststroke (1:33.18). Ellie Bergsten had a strong 500 free finishing 12th (7:49.11). Monica Luttrell scored for the Ladycats in her 200 IM. finished 15th (3:10.78). These ladies were joined by Ruth Walker to finish sixth in both the 200 medley relay (2:38.20) and 200 free relay (2:16.98). Advertisement
